t;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/regional-forums&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;Regional Forums&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Join College Board experts as they discuss the 2016 Trends in College Pricing, Trends in Student Aid, and Education Pays reports. Live from the College Board’s Western Regional Forum, the session will highlight findings that show higher education is linked to higher pay, job security, healthier behaviors, and more civic involvement. The session will also examine trends in college prices, financial aid, and student debt. Kate Peterson of Oregon State University will provide her reactions to the findings from a higher ed perspective.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What&lt;/strong&gt;: Trends in College Prices, Financial Aid, Student Debt, and Payoff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When&lt;/strong&gt;: Wednesday, February 8, 2017, 3:45-4:45 pm PT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where&lt;/strong&gt;: Watch at the listed time &lt;a href=&quot;http://goo.gl/DlR6fE&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt;. Or, if you’re attending the Western Regional Forum, join us in person: B1 Level, Laguna Beach III.&lt;/p&gt;
